      <description>&lt;p&gt;
Changelog eZ Newsletter 1.5.1 -&gt; 1.5.2&lt;br /&gt;
 -----------------------------------------------------------&lt;br /&gt;
 - Problems with the URLs in the newsletter send-outs when eZ&lt;br /&gt;
 Newsletter was installed in a subdirectory of the Apache document&lt;br /&gt;
 root (non-virtualhost mode)&lt;br /&gt;
 - Some stylesheet and HTML fixes for Internet Explorer&lt;br /&gt;
 - Bugfixes and improvements to the CSV subscriber import&lt;br /&gt;
 Changelog eZ Newsletter 1.0.0 -&gt; 1.5.1&lt;br /&gt;
 --------------------------------------------------------&lt;br /&gt;
 - Ability to set up most common configuration options via the&lt;br /&gt;
 Administration Interface (override dir)&lt;br /&gt;
 - Default templates for newsletter and front pages&lt;br /&gt;
 - Streamlined template code&lt;br /&gt;
 - Improved sendout scripts&lt;br /&gt;
 - Improved interface and better data validation&lt;br /&gt;
 - General bug fixes (including all reported bugs)&lt;br /&gt;
 Changelog Newsletter 0.1.0 Beta -&gt; 1.0.0 Stable&lt;br /&gt;
 ------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br /&gt;
 Bugs:&lt;br /&gt;
 -removed non RFC linebreaks bug in email generation&lt;br /&gt;
 -fixed css bug with Internet Explorer and div block&lt;br /&gt;
 -removed code for missing unsubscribe.php&lt;br /&gt;
 -removed transaction error on create newsletter&lt;br /&gt;
 -changed XML parser handling for pretext/posttext (changed XML API in&lt;br /&gt;
 &gt;3.8)&lt;br /&gt;
 -removing whitespaces in filepath of attachment files&lt;br /&gt;
 Design:&lt;br /&gt;
 -removed multiple topmenus for newsletter extension, only one newsletter&lt;br /&gt;
 topmenu&lt;br /&gt;
 -added left sidemenu with main newsletter functions&lt;br /&gt;
 -added submenu for each newslettertype with different statuses of&lt;br /&gt;
 newsletter and a link to inbox&lt;br /&gt;
 Fetures:&lt;br /&gt;
 -setting envelope return path parameter for MTA in ini file&lt;br /&gt;
 -define name of embedded attachment file in global-scope block &lt;br /&gt;
 -SMS outputformat included, custom transport class for provider&lt;br /&gt;
 required&lt;br /&gt;
 -subscribe/unsubscribe via email added&lt;br /&gt;
 -added firstname, mobile phone fields to profile&lt;br /&gt;
 -personalization by mobile phone, firstname added&lt;br /&gt;
 -improved user profile page, selecting outputformat and unsubscribing possible&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
 -extended csv import (firstname, mobile phone fields)&lt;br /&gt;
 -new feature search subscriber and directly modify/remove profile&lt;br /&gt;
 -added pretext/posttext definition in newslettertype&lt;br /&gt;
 -added pretext/posttext mapping to newsletter contentobject&lt;br /&gt;
 -added possibility of adding newsletter design extensions and selecting&lt;br /&gt;
 allowed designs in newslettertype&lt;br /&gt;
 -newsletter design selection while editing with preview image&lt;br /&gt;
 -one default design included&lt;br /&gt;
 -added newsletter recurrence on frontend and a cronjob for copy and archive&lt;br /&gt;
 newsletter&lt;br /&gt;
 -preview newsletter in target design/outpuformat while editing&lt;br /&gt;
 -send preview via email/SMS&lt;br /&gt;
 -senddate modifier definition in newslettertype&lt;br /&gt;
 -added File transport class for emails/SMS, enables pregeneration of&lt;br /&gt;
 newsletters and creates a file for each one&lt;br /&gt;
 Performance:&lt;br /&gt;
 -splitted newsletter sendout cronjobs&lt;br /&gt;
 [build_list+send_newsletter+send_sms+cluster_send]&lt;br /&gt;
 -added support for sendout with several SMTP servers (round robin&lt;br /&gt;
 method)&lt;br /&gt;
 -added index to database tables&lt;br /&gt;
 -possibility of pregenerating sending lists and newsletters/SMS with&lt;br /&gt;
 '-pregeneration' on build_list/send_newsletter cronjob&lt;br /&gt;
 -possibility of control newsettertypes directly via cronjob with&lt;br /&gt;
 '-type ' on build_list/send_newsletter cronjob&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
